(260, 'P', 1, 'Docs aren''t for your boss. They’re for the version of you three months from now who will have zero clue how this works.', 'Documentation as self-care', 'en'),
(261, 'P', 1, 'If the task is small enough, the pressure can''t catch you. Moving a mountain is just picking up one stone at a time.', 'Decomposition strategy', 'en'),
(262, 'P', 2, 'A good schedule isn''t for laziness; it’s a buffer for the "unexpected" disasters that are statistically guaranteed to happen.', 'Risk management', 'en'),
(263, 'P', 2, 'Agile isn''t about running fast; it''s about being able to pivot with minimal cost when you realize you''re running the wrong way.', 'True agility', 'en'),
(264, 'E', 0, 'Don’t reinvent the wheel unless you’re planning to add a turbocharger. Browse GitHub; don''t suffer in isolation.', 'Avoiding NIH syndrome', 'en'),
(265, 'E', 0, 'When in doubt, RTFM. Someone has already fallen into this pit; you don''t need to experience the fire personally.', 'Information retrieval', 'en'),
