(286, 'F', 1, 'A prompt isn''t a magic spell; it’s a contract. The more precise the terms, the less room there is for the AI to slack off.', 'The prompt contract', 'en'),
(287, 'F', 1, 'Errors are the system screaming for help. Don''t just copy-paste them to AI—explain what you were trying to achieve.', 'Error handling', 'en'),
(288, 'F', 1, 'Provide a clean interface to the world, even if your internal logic is a ball of yarn. Abstraction is a developer''s dignity.', 'Abstraction power', 'en'),
