(290, 'F', 2, 'The quality of your questions sets the ceiling for the answers. Precision is your ticket to cyber-telepathy.', 'Communication mastery', 'en'),
(291, 'D', 0, 'Don’t run expensive calculations in a core loop. It’s an insult to the CPU and a crime against the battery.', 'Performance correction', 'en'),
(292, 'E', 0, '"Fix it later" usually means "never." Technical debt has high interest—don''t let your future self hate you.', 'Technical debt warning', 'en'),
(293, 'P', 2, 'Agility isn''t about moving fast; it’s about having a small enough turning radius to pivot when you hit a dead end.', 'Essence of Agile', 'en'),
(294, 'L', 1, 'Look past the line of code to the data flow behind it. Your vision determines the lifespan of your bugs.', 'Global perspective', 'en'),
(295, 'D', 0, 'Operating on a production DB without a backup is cyber tightrope walking. There is no "Restart" after a fall.', 'High-risk behavior', 'en'),
(296, 'E', 1, 'CI/CD is your best friend. It won''t forget to run a build because of a breakup or a hangover.', 'Automation value', 'en'),
(297, 'F', 0, 'The less signal you provide, the louder the noise. AI is a logic engine, not a crystal ball.', 'Against mystical expectations', 'en'),
(298, 'L', 2, 'The ultimate aesthetic is "Nothing." No extra variables, no redundant logic—everything exists only because it is necessary.', 'Maximalist minimalism', 'en'),
(299, 'P', 1, 'Log your arguments with the AI. That’s not just a record; it’s a map of your own logical expansion.', 'Reflection habits', 'en'),
(300, 'D', 1, 'Architecture is taking a "mess of yarn" and putting it into "labeled boxes." You''ll thank yourself when it''s time to move.', 'Architectural insight', 'en'),
(301, 'E', 2, 'Real efficiency is reducing the cognitive load for the next person. If they can see your intent instantly, you’re a pro.', 'Long-term value', 'en'),
(302, 'L', 0, 'If the code works and you don’t know why, that’s not success—it’s a landmine. Go back and figure it out.', 'Against lucky results', 'en'),
(303, 'F', 2, 'AI is your exoskeleton, not your replacement. No matter how strong the suit, the pilot still needs to stay awake.', 'Human-AI relationship', 'en'),
(304, 'P', 0, 'When everything is going south, return to the standard procedure. Protocols aren''t for sunny days; they are for survival in the rain.', 'Against chaotic operations', 'en'),
(305, 'L', 1, 'Decoupling is the highest form of elegance. Don''t let anyone''s departure slow down your execution—in code and in life.', 'Decoupling philosophy', 'en'),
