(307, 'L', 0, 'Build yourself like a modular system. Even if one function crashes, the core should remain standing.', 'Modularity advice', 'en'),
(308, 'P', 2, 'The ultimate patience is restraint. Not writing a single line before you understand the "why" is the greatest mercy you can show a system.', 'Development rhythm', 'en'),
(309, 'L', 2, 'Architectural failure usually stems from trying to solve Day 100 problems on Day 1. Live in the now.', 'Against over-engineering', 'en'),
(310, 'P', 0, 'Those who refuse to debrief are doomed to fall into the same pit twice. Don''t give history a chance to repeat itself.', 'Against lack of summary', 'en'),
(311, 'L', 1, 'Logic without a defensive line relies on luck. Always assume external data is toxic; add your validation.', 'Defensive programming', 'en'),
