(320, 'P', 2, 'Leave some room for redundancy and buffers. Moving slower allows you to turn gracefully before you hit the wall.', 'Fault-tolerance philosophy', 'en'),
(321, 'L', 2, 'Minimalist code is the residue of high-intensity thinking. The finest ingredients require the simplest cooking.', 'Grand simplicity', 'en'),
(322, 'P', 0, 'If you can''t manage version numbers, you aren''t managing code—you''re managing a pile of random electronic garbage.', 'Version control awareness', 'en'),
(323, 'L', 1, 'Architectural intuition is forged in fire. Study enough failed designs, and you’ll recognize the right path instantly.', 'Architectural experience', 'en'),
(324, 'P', 1, 'The process should serve creativity. If it makes you feel suffocated, the process itself is rusted and needs refactoring.', 'Process iteration', 'en'),
(325, 'L', 0, 'Don’t code on vibes. Proving yourself wrong with data is more dignified than saying "I feel like" in a PR.', 'Objectivity', 'en'),
(326, 'P', 2, 'Admitting failure is wisdom. Cutting your losses to refactor is more efficient than building a skyscraper in a swamp.', 'Wisdom of stopping loss', 'en'),
