(330, 'P', 1, 'A good process should be invisible. You shouldn''t feel it constraining you, but you should know it’s protecting you.', 'Ideal process', 'en'),
(331, 'L', 0, 'Logical collapse usually starts with a "fix it later" compromise. Guard your logical boundaries.', 'Nip it in the bud', 'en'),
(332, 'P', 2, 'Sketch it out before you code. Even a rough drawing can lead you home when you’re lost in a forest of details.', 'Value of sketching', 'en'),
(333, 'L', 2, 'The highest form of logic is self-healing. A truly robust system doesn''t just resist failure; it embraces it, isolates it, and finds its own way back to equilibrium.', 'Resilience & Self-healing Philosophy', 'en'),
(334, 'E', 0, 'If a machine can do it, a human shouldn''t. Automation exists to save your inspiration for the moments where "only you" will do.', 'Automation awareness', 'en'),
